Package org.sbml.jsbml.validator.offline.factory

Class ConstraintFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbml.jsbml.validator.offline.factory.ConstraintFactory

  • public class ConstraintFactory
extends java.lang.Object
    Factory to be able to create ConstraintGroup to contains all constraints associated with one class or one attribute in one class.

    We scan all the interfaces and all the superclass of the class in order to be sure to include all the needed constraints. This factory is basically creating via reflection some ConstraintDeclaration instances which it use to create the ConstraintGroup.

    Since:
    1.2
    Author:
    Roman, rodrigue
    See Also:
    AbstractConstraintDeclaration.getInstance(String), ConstraintDeclaration.createConstraints(int, int, CHECK_CATEGORY[], ValidationContext), ConstraintDeclaration.createConstraints(int, int, String, ValidationContext), ConstraintDeclaration.addErrorCodesForCheck(Set, int, int, CHECK_CATEGORY, ValidationContext), ConstraintDeclaration.addErrorCodesForAttribute(Set, int, int, String, ValidationContext)

        Returns null if the class was already in the collectedClasses set.

        Parameters:

        attributeName - the attribute name to get constraint for

        version - the SBML version
        collectedClasses - the set of classes that we already created constraints for
        context - the validation context
        Returns:
        all constraints necessary to validate the attribute of the specified class. or null if the class was already in the collectedClasses set.
